        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1117311023" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer797892080683960784">At exactly 101th page, a thought passed through my mind - &quot;What could be alternative uses of this book?&quot;<br/><br/>First, it can really pass off as a nice and &quot;hard&quot; pillow, when you need one and not a real one handy. <br/><br/>Second, you can hurl it at someone, a vermin perhaps, if you want to really &quot;hurt&quot; that someone. (yes, I am talking about the hardcover edition, which I possess).<br/><br/>Third, if your arms don&apos;t reach to the top shelf, you can use it as a small stool, that can give you the required &quot;elevation&quot;.<br/><br/>But, </span>
  <span id="freeText797892080683960784" style="display:none">At exactly 101th page, a thought passed through my mind - "What could be alternative uses of this book?"<br /><br />First, it can really pass off as a nice and "hard" pillow, when you need one and not a real one handy. <br /><br />Second, you can hurl it at someone, a vermin perhaps, if you want to really "hurt" that someone. (yes, I am talking about the hardcover edition, which I possess).<br /><br />Third, if your arms don't reach to the top shelf, you can use it as a small stool, that can give you the required "elevation".<br /><br />But, if you go for its intended use and read it instead, chances are that you could find a brilliant nail-biting, heart-pounding, edge-of-the-seat, bollywood blockbuster. <br /><br />I couldn't.<br />The fault is in me. <br /><br />Good Luck. <br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="797892080683960784" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
